<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow, back on Monday.</em></p><h2 style=3D"font-weight=
: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;=
 letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bo=
ttom-style: dotted; padding-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 0=
;">Tesla &amp; Bitcoin</h2><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Apparently someone =
sat Elon Musk down and told him=C2=A0where Bitcoins come from? Yesterday <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23834416.275264/aHR0=
cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9lbG9ubXVzay9zdGF0dXMvMTM5MjYwMjA0MTAyNTg0MzIwMw/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf201de11" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;">he tweeted</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">Tesla has suspended vehicle purchases using Bitcoin. We are concerned=
 about rapidly increasing use of fossil fuels for Bitcoin mining and transa=
ctions, especially coal, which has the worst emissions of any fuel.</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Cryptocurrency is a good idea on many levels and w=
e believe it has a promising future, but this cannot come at great cost to =
the environment.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tesla will not be selling =
any Bitcoin and we intend to use it for transactions as soon as mining tran=
sitions to more sustainable energy. We are also looking at other cryptocurr=
encies that use &lt;1% of Bitcoin=E2=80=99s energy/transaction.</p></blockq=
uote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elon Musk=E2=80=99s whims are among the m=
ain drivers of Bitcoin=E2=80=99s price, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/23834416.275264/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZ=
XdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMTIvbXVzay1zYXlzLXRlc2xhLXN1c3BlbmRpbmctYml0Y29p=
bi1wdXJjaGFzZXMtY2l0aW5nLWVuZXJneS11c2U/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBce1097f5" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> so</a>:</=
p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The largest cryptocurrency dropp=
ed as much as 15% to just above $46,000, before paring some of the retreat.=
 It was down about 6% to $51,210 as of 7:03 a.m. in London on Thursday. Oth=
er tokens such Ether and Dogecoin also slid. The rush to sell briefly cause=
d outages at some cryptocurrency exchanges.=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Look, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/23834416.275264/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydG=
ljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMjIvZWxlY3RyaWMtYmlsbHMtYXJlLWEtZ2FtYmxlLXRvbw/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cBcb099be7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">you know what I think</a>. The funny move here would be if T=
esla Inc. had dumped all its Bitcoins at the highs. (It <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23834416.275264/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb=
21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDQtMjgvZWxvbi1tdXNrLW1hZGUtdGVz=
bGEtc29tZS1tb25leS1vbi1iaXRjb2lu/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB40c29017" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> sold about 10%</=
a> of its Bitcoins in March =E2=80=9Cessentially to prove liquidity of Bitc=
oin,=E2=80=9D but I suppose that could have been a test run for a larger sa=
le?) And then maybe gone short too for good measure. And then Elon Musk ann=
ounces =E2=80=9Coh actually Bitcoin is bad now lol,=E2=80=9D and the price =
plummets, and he grins his impish grin and we=E2=80=99re all like oh, Elon,=
 you got us again.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have no reason to beli=
eve that this is what happened, though I note that=C2=A0<em>technically=C2=
=A0</em>Musk=E2=80=99s=C2=A0statement says that Tesla =E2=80=9C<em>will not=
 </em>be<em>=C2=A0</em>selling any=C2=A0Bitcoin,=E2=80=9D not that it <em>h=
asn=E2=80=99t already</em>. I=E2=80=99m just saying,=C2=A0if <em>I=C2=A0</e=
m>was Elon Musk, that=E2=80=99s what I would do. Then of course I=E2=80=99d=
 buy more Bitcoins after the price falls, I=E2=80=99d tweet =E2=80=9CBitcoi=
n is great again,=E2=80=9D the price would go up, I=E2=80=99d sell my Bitco=
ins, I=E2=80=99d tweet =E2=80=9Coh no it=E2=80=99s bad again,=E2=80=9D the =
price would go down, I=E2=80=99d buy more Bitcoins, I=E2=80=99d tweet =E2=
=80=9Cback to great,=E2=80=9D etc. etc. etc. This would be vastly more prof=
itable, for Tesla, than making cars, and it would capitalize on Musk=E2=80=
=99s core skill of trolling people on Twitter. How long do you think he cou=
ld keep this up? I think the answer is=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cfar longer than I coul=
d remain sane while watching it happen.=E2=80=9D[1]=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin: 16px 0;">Again, though, I don=E2=80=99t think this is what happened; =
I assume that Tesla has kept most of its Bitcoin stash and is not profiting=
 from Musk=E2=80=99s tweets. As far as I can tell he has only limited inter=
est in manipulating the price of Bitcoin =E2=80=94=C2=A0or Dogecoin, or Tes=
la stock, or the other assets whose prices he can control=C2=A0with his twe=
ets =E2=80=94=C2=A0<em>for profit</em>. He=E2=80=99ll do it for fun, sure, =
occasionally, but not in a way that serves his rational self-interest. I as=
sume that what actually happened is pretty much what Musk said: He got into=
 cryptocurrency on a whim because it fit with his image of being fun and fu=
turistic and annoying, and then someone explained to him that it doesn=E2=
=80=99t fit with his image of being good for the environment, and on a whim=
 he decided to cool it on the Bitcoin stuff for a while.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And when Elon Musk announces a decision on Twitter, he=
 will often <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/238344=
16.275264/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtM=
TMvbXVzay1zLWJpdGNvaW4tYmFja3BlZGFsaW5nLWlzLWxhdGVzdC1pbi1sb25nLWxpbmUtb2Yt=
dHVybmFib3V0cw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6f55d9a6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> stick with that decision</a> for h=
ours, sometimes even days at a time. Surely by next week he=E2=80=99ll be t=
weeting, like, =E2=80=9Cwe are building a giant battery in the desert to mi=
ne Bitcoin, Bitcoin is good again, you can use it to pay for Teslas,=E2=80=
=9D and the price will shoot back up, and I=E2=80=99ll once again hit the b=
utton that auto-generates this column.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My B=
loomberg Opinion colleague Liam Denning <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/23834416.275264/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMTMvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWNvbnZlbmllbnRseS1pZ25vcmVk=
LWJpdGNvaW4tcy1pbmNvbnZlbmllbnQtdHJ1dGg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8d980cbf" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> points ou=
t</a> that =E2=80=9CMusk=E2=80=99s move may also indicate that Teslas weren=
=E2=80=99t flying off the shelves as a result of accepting Bitcoin payment,=
=E2=80=9D and in fact it=E2=80=99s not entirely clear whether Tesla has sol=
d any cars for Bitcoins.[2] I hope it hasn=E2=80=99t. I hope Musk can make =
the price of Bitcoin go up or down by 10%=C2=A0by announcing that Tesla wil=
l or will not accept Bitcoins for cars, without ever actually accepting any=
 Bitcoins for any cars either way. There=E2=80=99s something pure about tha=
t: The price of Bitcoin depends on Elon Musk=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>attitude=C2=
=A0</em>toward it, not on the existence of any grubby commercial transactio=
ns in which Bitcoins are exchanged for cars.[3] The source of value for Bit=
coin is not its=C2=A0<em>use as a currency=C2=A0</em>or=C2=A0<em>economic i=
mportance</em>; the source of value for Bitcoin =E2=80=94=C2=A0for everythi=
ng =E2=80=94=C2=A0is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/23834416.275264/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVz=
LzIwMjEtMDItMDgvZWxvbi1tdXNrLXdvcmtzLWhpcy1tYWdpYy1vbi1kb2dlY29pbi1hbmQtYml=
0Y29pbg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3bd992eb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">simple proximity to Elon Musk</a>.</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway, since Musk is looking for alternatives,=C2=
=A0I have a coin that uses &lt;1% of Bitcoin=E2=80=99s energy per transacti=
on!=C2=A0It is called ExcelCoin.[4] Instead of relying on proof-of-work, bu=
rning tons of energy to mine coins to reward people for keeping track of th=
e ledger of transactions, as Bitcoin does, ExcelCoin relies on me keeping t=
rack of the list of transactions in Microsoft Excel. If you want to buy Exc=
elCoins, you just wire me money and I add some ExcelCoins to the line with =
your name on it, in my Excel spreadsheet. If you want to buy a Tesla with E=
xcelCoins,=C2=A0you send me an email saying =E2=80=9Csend my ExcelCoins to =
Tesla,=E2=80=9D I deduct the ExcelCoins from your line in Excel and add the=
m to Tesla=E2=80=99s line, and I send Tesla an email saying =E2=80=9Cyou=E2=
=80=99ve got the ExcelCoins, hand over the car.=E2=80=9D If you want to red=
eem your ExcelCoins for dollars, well, well, well, well, well, well, let=E2=
=80=99s discuss that some other time.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also =
dollars, banks pretty much do this with dollars! They use more electricity =
than I do running Excel but, you know.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Else=
where in <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23834416.=
275264/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmR0di5jb20vb2ZmYmVhdC9tYXJrLXp1Y2tlcmJlcmdzLWdvYXQt=
cGljLXNwYXJrcy1iaXRjb2luLXNwZWN1bGF0aW9uLWRldGFpbHMtaGVyZS0yNDM5NjQ4/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB750e3458" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">tech celebrities ambiguously endorsing=C2=A0Bitcoin</a>:=
</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mark Zuckerberg shared a pictu=
re of his pet goats on Monday, introducing them to the world as Bitcoin and=
 Max. The picture quickly set social media abuzz with speculation about the=
 significance of the name "Bitcoin". Bitcoin investors took it as an endors=
ement of the cryptocurrency from the Facebook founder, while meme-makers to=
ok the opportunity and flooded social media with hilarious memes.=C2=A0</p>=
</blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Not a bad effort, but I don=E2=80=
=99t think Zuckerberg is going to steal back much Bitcoin-related attention=
 from Musk with a couple of goats. Maybe if he tweets =E2=80=9CI <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23834416.275264/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAxOS8wMS8yNC9tYXJrLXp1Y2tlcmJlcmctb25jZS1raWxsZWQtYS1nb2F=
0LS1hbmQtc2VydmVkLWl0LXRvLWphY2stZG9yc2V5LS5odG1sIzp-OnRleHQ9SXQncyUyMGElMj=
BkaW5uZXIlMjB0aGUlMjBUd2l0dGVyLGFuZCUyMHNlbnQlMjB0byUyMHRoZSUyMGJ1dGNoZXIu/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB176f32c4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">killed Bitcoin with my own two hands</a> and then =
roasted it and served it to Elon Musk=C2=A0for dinner,=E2=80=9D that might =
do it.</p><h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&qu=
ot;, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; padding-bottom: 5px; =
margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 0;">DarkSide=C2=A0</h2><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">My <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23834=
416.275264/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgt=
MDgtMTIvdGhlLTEwLWxhd3Mtb2YtaW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW5n/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2=
aeda8f6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #00=
0000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bo=
ttom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">F=
ifth Law of Insider Trading</a> says that you should not insider trade <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/23834416.275264/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTctMDQtMjEvanVpY2Uta=
GFja2luZy1hbmQtbW9ydGdhZ2UtdGVjaA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB37ca62cb" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> by planting bom=
bs at a company and buying put options on its stock</a>.[5] This law exists=
 because someone did it, to Borussia Dortmund GmbH, and got in trouble. I s=
ometimes extend the Fifth Law metaphorically to mean that you should not be=
